OL,3,CArrears on household bills surge 25%
OL,4,Camong those in debt, charity says
OL,6,FStepChange said fewer clients were now
OL,7,Fciting the cost of living as their
OL,8,Fmain reason for debt despite overall
OL,9,Fdebt levels rising significantly, and
OL,10,Fmany had struggled to rebuild
OL,11,Ffinancial stability after "years of
OL,12,Feconomic turmoil".
OL,14,FIn 2024, three in five clients (60%)
OL,15,Fwere in some form of employment, up
OL,16,Ffrom 59% and 56% in 2023 and 2022
OL,17,Frespectively.
OL,19,FThe average monthly income among
OL,20,Fclients was also up 7% year on year,
OL,21,Fstanding at #1,874 in 2024.
